airline.description: United Airlines, Inc. is a major American airline headquartered in Chicago, Illinois. It was founded in 1926 and has since grown to become one of the largest airlines in the world, offering domestic and international flights to numerous destinations. United Airlines is known for its broad network, fleet diversity, and partnerships with global airline alliances such as Star Alliance. It provides a wide range of services to passengers, including various classes of service, in-flight entertainment, and loyalty programs such as MileagePlus, offering frequent flyers the chance to earn miles for travel rewards.
